## Anti-patterns (DO NOT do)

- ❌ Client-side fetch to RLS-protected tables · always go through Server Actions
- ❌ Using service-role key client-side · `createAdminClient()` is server-only
- ❌ Bypassing the role-guard at the SA layer "because RLS will catch it" · dual-layer is the contract
- ❌ Logging PII in audit_logs · audit payload structure is invariant: `{ resource_id, status_to, transitioned_at, ... }` with NO names/emails/phones
- ❌ DELETE on audit_logs · the audit table is INSERT-only by RLS · never UPDATE either
- ❌ `select("*")` on user-facing surfaces · always name columns to prevent accidental admin-column leak

